name: The eighth incarnation. Mongoose
description:
The mycelium once again released me, filling me with energy for a new incarnation.

I was born a mongoose. We had a big family - dad, several moms and many children. 

From birth, I was not a leader, but I had to become one. Games didn't interest me much. I was very curious and tried to stay close to Dad. So, I became the youngest hunter in our pack. At first I was in support, and eventually I became a presenter. 

I enjoyed hunting alone. Rats are interesting, insidious, strong, but very tasty prey. Catching them, I liked the most. Many times in search of rats, I came across snakes. 

I wanted to make friends with the first snake. She charmed me. But at one point, when I was relaxed, she rushed at me in an attempt to kill me. I remembered Dad's story about the insidiousness of snakes, dodged, hit her and ran away. 

So, I learned the insidiousness of snakes. Every subsequent snake I met was killed. Snakes are delicious, but it's sickening to eat them.

I loved the nights. Sitting in a tree, I often looked at the stars. Looking at the stars, I met my first female. With all the other females, the first thing I did was sit on the same branch and look at the stars. And a lot of my kids were sitting on that bitch. 

And I died in a fight with an owl who decided to visit our territory.
